# Delivery workflow (always follow)

> **Compliance:** `agents-mandatory.mdc` is binding. All `.cursor/rules/` apply; do not skip steps.

Every task—planning, review, fix, test, or implementation—must follow this sequence.

## 1. Plan

- Restate goal, acceptance criteria, and affected layers (UI, domain, data, Supabase, CI, QA).
- Read existing code and `.cursor/rules/` before designing; prefer extending over inventing.
- Call out risks: i18n (8 locales), persistence/sync, keyboard/scroll, AI read-only vs editable data, wide layout (≥600dp), dark theme, platform splits.
- Keep scope minimal: smallest correct change.

## 2. Implement

- Match clean architecture and naming; reuse shared components (see `ui-ux-compose.mdc`).
- No drive-by refactors, secrets in repo, or hardcoded user-facing strings (`i18n-multilingual.mdc`).
- `expect`/`actual` only when no multiplatform library exists.
- Navigation: `AppNavigator` + `AppRoute` — not Voyager (catalog only, unused).

## 3. Test

- **Unit** (`commonTest`): domain, screen models, repositories, codecs, i18n parity, navigation contracts.
- **Instrumented** (`androidInstrumentedTest`): critical UX with `testTag`s; `Instrumented*Fakes`, not production network.
- **Supabase** (when touching invites/migrations): `scripts/verify-supabase-household.sh`, edge Deno tests if helpers change.
- Update `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` when user-facing flows change (bump `version`).
- Run before done: `./gradlew :composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` (+ `compileDebugAndroidTestKotlinAndroid` if UI changed).

## 4. Review

Follow `review-commit.mdc` self-review checklist: UX states, architecture boundaries, security, i18n, design system, tests, QA YAML.

## 5. CI/CD & release

- **PR:** push feature branch → PR to `main` → CI (Android unit, instrumented, Supabase migrations) → squash merge.
- **Release:** manual dispatch only after merge — `gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=release -f version_bump=patch`.
- Firebase distribute embeds QA checklist from `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml`.
- iOS compile: manual dispatch or local `./gradlew :composeApp:compileKotlinIosSimulatorArm64` (CI iOS job disabled for cost).

## Definition of done

Feature works on target platforms; tests added/updated and passing; strings localized in all 8 locales; manual QA steps in Firebase YAML when flows change; no new linter issues in touched files; review-commit checklist satisfied.
